I'm wondering if there is something to prevent us from doing

```suggestion
      const string& fname, std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFile>* result) {
      return NewRandomAccessFile(fname, nullptr, result);
  }

  virtual tensorflow::Status NewRandomAccessFile(
      const string& fname, TransactionToken* token,
      std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFile>* result) = 0;
```

This way we have the old methods redirect to the new ones by default and the new ones still use the style of having output parameters last.

